    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Baltimore</placeName>, <date>May 24th 64</date></p>
            <p>Dr Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I enclose an English<lb/> paraphrase of the Hebrew<lb/> Enigma in yr
                last Occident,<lb/> and if you think it worthy<lb/> of insertion in the next<lb/>
                number, it is at your service.<lb/> I hope to see you, as usual,<lb/> when you visit
                    <placeName>Balto.</placeName> when<lb/> by shewing you a literal<lb/> copy you
                will at once<lb/> identify the writer as</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">The Translator</persName>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philada.</placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>The beginning &amp; end of the mightiest Heroes</p>
            <p>The world ever boasted, on land or on sea,</p>
            <p>I was ere Creation &amp; was not created,</p>
            <p>Enclosed in the tomb, yet not ceasing to be.</p>
            <p/>
            <p>Nor yet shall I cease when time's record is ended,</p>
            <p>And the nations of earth have to chaos returned:</p>
            <p>Man's hand could not keep me united or blended,</p>
            <p>And on me the eye of the Lord hath not burned.</p>
            <p/>
            <p>Yet in Heaven &amp; earth I am recognized wholly,</p>
            <p>And dwell with the dead &amp; the living around.</p>
            <p>Associate of wisdom &amp; foe to all folly,</p>
            <p>In the seat of the scorners I could not be found.</p>
            <p/>
            <p>No form or resemblance of form doth surround me,</p>
            <p>No body corporeal or subject to death,</p>
            <p>Not formed from the clay, nor has earth ever bound me;</p>
            <p>No spirit, no soul, &amp; no animate breath.</p>
            <p/>
            <p>If knowledge delights thee &amp; wisdom's way only,</p>
            <p>Say what is my name, &amp; my dwelling declare.</p>
            <p>Depart to the wilderness arid &amp; lonely,</p>
            <p>And seek me in deserts all blighted &amp; bare.</p>
            <p/>
            <p>For only in solitudes wasted &amp; dreary,</p>
            <p>Removed from the present &amp; dead to the past,</p>
            <p>There's quiet from trouble &amp; rest for the weary,</p>
            <p>And stillness before thee, &amp; silence at last.</p>
        </body>
